05/01/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian ambassadors from all over the world are gathering on Wednesday (January 5th) in Belgrade for a conference organised by the foreign ministry. 
Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic will open the two-day event and President Boris Tadic will address the participants. 
Slovak Foreign Minister Mikulas Dzurinda is attending as a special guest. 
(Beta, Tanjug, RTS - 05/01/11)
